A t-shirt showing a mountain and deer and the slogan “Respect Nature.” A black polo shirt with black, white, and red piping and a small circular logo.
It’s a black sun, a common neo-Nazi symbol adapted from a floor mosaic in Heinrich Himmler’s SS Generals’ Hall.
That logo on the polo shirt?
Far-right fashion in Europe has become a niche industry over the past decade.
And those who have their eyes on the far-right fashion scene in Europe think the U.S. is next.